{
  "name": "clean-up-the-final-video-20260406-0959",
  "idea": "Clean up the final video badge and shot creation flow in the video editor timeline. Three issues to fix:\n\n1. SHOT GROUP NOT APPEARING AFTER CREATE: createShotWithGenerationsPath in src/shared/hooks/shotCreation/shotCreationPaths.ts line 264 calls invalidateShotsQueries with refetchType:'inactive' which skips the active ShotsContext query. Same issue on line 204 for createShotWithFilesPath. Fix: remove refetchType:'inactive' so active queries refetch too.\n\n2. FINAL VIDEO BADGE KEEPS REAPPEARING: dismissedShotIds in useFinalVideoAvailable.ts uses useState which resets on component remount. Move to a module-level Set (like useStaleVariants uses for dismissedAssetKeys at line 30) so it survives remounts. Also need to dismiss based on finalVideo.id (not shotId) so newer final videos for the same shot still show the badge.\n\n3. BADGE SHOWS AFTER SWITCHING TO FINAL VIDEO: After applyEdit fires, the shot group recalculates. If the replaced video clip's generationId happens to match a shot image, the group re-forms and hasFinalVideo is still true (because finalVideoShotIds still includes it during the render before dismiss takes effect). The dismiss-before-switch approach was attempted but timing issues remain. Need a more robust solution - possibly check if any clip in the group is already using the final video asset, and suppress the badge in that case.\n\nKey files:\n- src/shared/hooks/shotCreation/shotCreationPaths.ts (lines 204, 264)\n- src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useFinalVideoAvailable.ts\n- src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useShotGroups.ts\n- src/tools/video-editor/components/TimelineEditor/TimelineCanvas.tsx\n- src/tools/video-editor/components/TimelineEditor/TimelineEditor.tsx\n- src/tools/travel-between-images/hooks/video/useShotFinalVideos.ts",
